File: platform/browser-extension/src/sanitize-svg.ts, lines 278-308.

The bug: When processing elements inside a stripped subtree (strippedDepth > 0), the code increments strippedDepth on opening tags (line 304) but the closing tag handler (around line 282) falls through without decrementing. After the outermost disallowed element closes and strippedDepth reaches 0, any allowed elements that were opened inside it left strippedDepth elevated, so subsequent content is incorrectly stripped.

Fix: In the closing tag handler, when strippedDepth > 0, decrement strippedDepth and continue (don't emit the closing tag). The logic should be:
```
if (strippedDepth > 0) {
  strippedDepth--;
  continue; // or return
}
```

Add unit tests for the specific cases mentioned in acceptance criteria. Check if there's an existing test file for sanitize-svg.

The pattern `err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err)` appears 62 times across the codebase, with 38 occurrences in platform/browser-extension/src/browser-commands.ts alone.

Create in platform/shared/src/index.ts:
```typescript
export function toErrorMessage(err: unknown): string {
  return err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);
}
```

For browser-extension (which may not import from shared): either add the function locally in browser-extension/src/utils.ts, or check if the build resolves workspace imports. The 38 occurrences in browser-commands.ts are the biggest win.

Use find-and-replace carefully — some occurrences may have slight variations (e.g., `(error as Error).message` or `error instanceof Error ? error.message : ...`). Search for all variants.
